    "comments" : [
      {
        "id" : "ca5cf02b-16c3-4d93-a6ed-8462b03fdf9f",
        "parentId" : null,
        "authorId" : "a3f1fdb0-47ad-411e-b63d-af6fc71a1fa6",
        "body" : "Why does this version constraint not match the one above?\n",
        "createdAt" : "2016-09-19T01:33:26Z",
        "updatedAt" : "2016-09-21T17:55:41Z",
        "lastEditedBy" : "a3f1fdb0-47ad-411e-b63d-af6fc71a1fa6",
        "tags" : [
        ]
      },
      {
        "id" : "d03a5a1d-9125-4e11-a37e-9736a657ddc9",
        "parentId" : "ca5cf02b-16c3-4d93-a6ed-8462b03fdf9f",
        "authorId" : "ba498a7b-47cf-4566-88fb-0d15ecc93866",
        "body" : "The short answer is \"because that's what upstream has declared.\"\n\nsetup.py [says](https://github.com/openstack/oslo.utils/blob/3.16.0/setup.py#L28):\n\n``` python\nsetup_requires=['pbr>=1.8'],\n```\n\nbut requirements.txt [says](https://github.com/openstack/oslo.utils/blob/3.16.0/requirements.txt#L10)\n\n``` python\npbr>=1.6 # Apache-2.0\n```\n\nThe upstream change that declared this 1.6/1.8 requirement is [here](https://review.openstack.org/#/c/224330/), the commit description explains that we need `pbr>=1.8` at setup/build-time to handle comments in marker lines - but there's a weaker version requirement at runtime since we only need to be able to return version and other information from the (more stable) dist-info metadata.\n\nTo complicate it further, oslo.utils doesn't actually use pbr at run-time, but the requirement is necessary (aiui) to force setuptools/pbr to install packages in the correct order when a 3rd-party requires both oslo.utils _and_ pbr.  See https://bugs.launchpad.net/pbr/+bug/1384919\n\nMore generally: Should we be making these sorts of efforts to investigate and double-guess upstream's metadata declarations?  I feel like I've just spent an hour of my life only to reach the unsurprising conclusion that upstream knows more about their software than I do.  @jakirkham, what's the actual issue here?\n",
        "createdAt" : "2016-09-19T02:29:04Z",
        "updatedAt" : "2016-09-21T17:55:41Z",
        "lastEditedBy" : "ba498a7b-47cf-4566-88fb-0d15ecc93866",
        "tags" : [
        ]
      },
      {
        "id" : "682378d9-9965-4083-8af3-3251071f658e",
        "parentId" : "ca5cf02b-16c3-4d93-a6ed-8462b03fdf9f",
        "authorId" : "8daadbe3-650b-47d3-bfc7-2053c91301ec",
        "body" : "We've seen this issue in other `oslo` builds as well.\n",
        "createdAt" : "2016-09-19T04:36:11Z",
        "updatedAt" : "2016-09-21T17:55:41Z",
        "lastEditedBy" : "8daadbe3-650b-47d3-bfc7-2053c91301ec",
        "tags" : [
